If your parents love you they will think you can finally decide for your self, if they treat you like a baby stand up for you self…
[/quote]I think they are doing this because they love him. It’s because they want to make sure he makes friends and stays healthy. Being on your computer all day is not healthy or very good for you socially. Obviously completely removing all computer use is a bit much, but limiting it is totally acceptable and what a parent should do. It also helps children not become spoiled brats. One of my friends is spoiled rotten, and one of the reasons he is is because his parents let him do whatever he wants. He is either on the computer or other video games all day long. I am only allowed to play console games on weekends or special occasions. Obviously at first I thought this was outrageous, but as I am growing older I realize why my parents did it, and I am glad they did.

That’s a lot of words for you David, I’m proud
[/quote]You obviously don’t read all of my posts. :)[/quote]
